definition.value: A general term that describes a congenital defect in the iliac wing resulting from abnormal development.
An abnormal backward rotation of the hip relative to the knee such that the hips are externally rotated with the foot pointed outward instead of straight ahead (out-toeing).

label.value: Early ossification of capital femoral epiphyses

definition.value: A developmental defect characterized by lack of development of the pubis bone.

label.value: Absent ossification of capital femoral epiphysis

definition.value: Underdevelopment of the lower branch of the pubis bone (inferior pubic ramus).

label.value: obsolete Dislocation of the femoral head

definition.value: Underdevelopment of a ramus (branch) of the pubic bone.
